represents is one point across

00:19:01.110 --> 00:19:04.920
the entire set of photos
that we identified.

00:19:04.920 --> 00:19:07.760
Each of these points identifies
a point that was

00:19:07.760 --> 00:19:12.220
matched in a set of pixels
across all of these photos.

00:19:12.220 --> 00:19:16.190
And you can see, although the 3D
point cloud isn't complete,

00:19:16.190 --> 00:19:20.050
you can clearly see that this
is a representation of the

00:19:20.050 --> 00:19:22.170
Notre Dame Cathedral.

00:19:22.170 --> 00:19:25.880
So what do we do once we have
this 3D point cloud?

00:19:25.880 --> 00:19:28.200
The next step is, again,
as I said earlier--

00:19:28.200 --> 00:19:31.520
we have on the order of tens of
thousands of photos of the

00:19:31.520 --> 00:19:32.940
Notre Dame.

00:19:32.940 --> 00:19:36.240
If I were to show you all of
those, that would look like a

00:19:36.240 --> 00:19:42.000
tour of your poor cousin's trip
