00:23:08.240 --> 00:23:11.020
So now we have a set of photos,
and we know where

00:23:11.020 --> 00:23:13.220
those photos were taken from.

00:23:13.220 --> 00:23:15.100
What's the next step?

00:23:15.100 --> 00:23:18.120
What Jonah mentioned earlier
when he was giving you a very

00:23:18.120 --> 00:23:21.440
high level overview of these
photo tours is, we want to

00:23:21.440 --> 00:23:27.340
take into account how
cinematographers have really

00:23:27.340 --> 00:23:31.600
thought about how to navigate
through a scene, create a

00:23:31.600 --> 00:23:35.790
camera motion model that really
reflects that and gives

00:23:35.790 --> 00:23:38.610
you a very smooth, fluid motion

00:23:38.610 --> 00:23:40.300
throughout the entire scene.

00:23:40.300 --> 00:23:43.390
So we take all the canonical
photos and arrange them such

00:23:43.390 --> 00:23:47.200
that you can create a path from
camera position to camera

00:23:47.200 --> 00:23:50.840
position that feels very
fluid and natural.

00:23:50.840 --> 00:23:52.450
And that's what this reflects.

00:23:52.450 --> 00:23:55.470
We're going from the photo on
